# Template Analysis – GitHub Project Templates

| Template Name        | Columns / Workflow                          | Automation Features                          | Agile Suitability |
|---------------------|---------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------|------------------|
| Basic Kanban        | To Do, In Progress, Done                    | No automation                                | Good for simple projects |
| Automated Kanban    | To Do, In Progress, Done                    | Auto-moves issues based on status updates    | Excellent for Agile teams |
| Bug Triage          | New, Needs Review, In Progress, Done        | Auto-labeling and issue prioritization       | Best for maintenance projects |
| Team Planning       | Backlog, Ready, In Progress, Done           | Supports planning and prioritization         | Good for sprint planning |

---

## ✅ Justification

The **Automated Kanban template** was selected for the Computer Repair Management System.

This template is most suitable because:

- It supports **automation**, which reduces manual task tracking.
- Issues automatically move between columns when updated (e.g., closed → Done).
- It aligns with **Agile principles** such as continuous delivery and iterative progress.
- It works well with **user stories and sprint tasks** from Assignment 6.
- It improves efficiency for tracking repair workflows like:
  - Device intake
  - Repair progress
  - Testing
  - Completion

Compared to Basic Kanban, it saves time. Compared to Bug Triage, it is more suitable for development rather than just fixing issues.

Therefore, Automated Kanban best supports the workflow of the system.
